		{
			"type": "paragraph",
			"children": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "Crystal Bay",
					"url": "https://goo.gl/maps/PYr6nzNW9rRQZhV2A",
					"bold": true
				},
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "– or the Crystal Clear Bay, located on the west side of the island. Here, you’ll find somewhat cooler water, but a beautiful coral reef with plenty of colorful fish. The beach isn’t very large, and there isn’t much shade, but you can use paid sunbeds or the palm trees at the edge. Especially in the evening before sunset, expect a lot of people. This is the best spot for sunset watching. During the day, you’ll encounter plenty of tour boats bringing snorkeling tourists. If you head south along the beach up the stairs, after a while, you’ll reach another hidden and peaceful beach,"
				},
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "Pandan Beach",
					"url": "https://goo.gl/maps/U2pAhm9Zb7rtadS47",
					"bold": true
				},
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": ", where you don’t have to expect crowds of tourists. However, there is a refreshment stand here as well."
				}
			]
		},
